# Spring Boot integration testing (external cherry-pick)

Source: [jabrena/cursor-rules-java](https://github.com/jabrena/cursor-rules-java) rule 312 — adapted for your monorepo (Gradle, not Maven).

## Integration test placement

- Suffix: `*IT` or `*IntegrationTest` under `src/test/java`.
- Run with `./gradlew integrationTest` when separated; else included in `test` task per repo.

## External dependencies

- **HTTP downstream:** WireMock (`@AutoConfigureWireMock` or programmatic stub).
- **Azure / DB:** prefer testcontainers or in-memory fakes already in repo; do not add new infra without wiki decision.
- **Time:** inject `Clock` or use fixed `Instant` — no `Thread.sleep` in tests.

## Agentic Loop alignment

- Follow existing repo patterns (`my-service-aggregator`, `cdp-your-service-api-java`).
- Integration tests prove **wiring + contract**, not every branch (unit tests cover branches).
- JaCoCo measured packages still apply — integration tests count toward line ratio.

## Conflicts

Agentic Loop [`java-springboot-standards.mdc`](../java-springboot-standards.mdc) and [`service-quality-drill.mdc`](../service-quality-drill.mdc) take precedence.
